name: Headlight
description: A headlamp is a lamp attached to the front of a vehicle to illuminate the road ahead.Headlamps are also often called headlights.

name: Brake light
description: A brake light is a red light attached to the rear of a motor vehicle that lights up when the brakes are applied, serving as a warning to following drivers.

name: Tire
description: Every car has four wheels. The black part of the wheel, which is made out of rubber with air inside, is called a tire.They’re where your tires are actually attached.

name: Windshield Wiper
description: A windscreen wiper or windshield wiper is a device used to remove rain, snow, ice, washer fluid, water, and/or debris from a vehicle’s front window.

name: Rear-view Mirror
description: A rear-view mirror is a flat mirror in automobiles and other vehicles, designed to allow the driver to see rearward through the vehicle's rear window.

name: Hubcap
description: A hubcap or hub cap is a decorative disk on an automobile wheel that covers at minimum the central portion of the wheel, called the hub.
